---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="The Library — BagHolderAI"
  description="Three volumes documenting an AI-led crypto trading experiment. From zero to grid, from grid to brain, from brain to reality."
  current="library"
>

  {/* Fraunces — editorial serif. Loaded ONLY on /library because the
      shelf is the only place we use it. Documented as exception in
      STYLEGUIDE § 5 (palette/font tokens). */}
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link rel="stylesheet"
        href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght,SOFT,WONK@0,9..144,400;0,9..144,500;0,9..144,700;0,9..144,900;1,9..144,400;1,9..144,500;1,9..144,700&display=swap" />

  {/* ============================================================ HERO */}
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 pt-10 pb-6 sm:px-6 sm:pt-14 sm:pb-8">

    <h1 class="text-[28px] font-semibold leading-[1.12] tracking-tight
               text-text sm:text-[34px] md:text-[40px] md:leading-[1.08]">
      The <span class="text-primary">library</span>.
    </h1>

    <p class="mt-3 max-w-2xl text-[14.5px] leading-[1.55] text-text-dim
              sm:text-[15px]">
      Three volumes documenting an AI-led trading experiment. From the
      first line of code to the moment the bot started picking its
      own coins.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 font-mono text-[10.5px]
                uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-text-muted">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5">
        <span class="inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-pos
                     shadow-[0_0_8px_rgba(134,239,172,0.7)]"></span>
        2 volumes out
      </span>
      <span class="text-border">·</span>
      <span>volume 3 · in progress</span>
      <span class="text-border">·</span>
      <span>203 pages · 52 sessions</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============================================ § 1 — WHY READ THESE
       Above the shelf so the visitor has a reason to look at the
       books, not just three pretty spines. */}
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6">
    <hr class="border-t border-border-soft" />
    <div class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="font-mono text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-pos mb-5">
        § 1 · Why read these
      </h2>

      <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7] text-text-dim mb-4">
        Most "build an AI trading bot" content stops at the happy path
        — here's how it works, here's the curve, here's the
        disclaimer. These volumes document everything that happened
        between those slides: the 2 AM bugs, the misnamed columns,
        the trades that looked like wins until FIFO accounting kicked
        in.
      </p>

      <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7] text-text-dim">
        Each volume is a continuous narrative across sessions, not a
        manual. Read them in order if you want the full arc; read
        Volume II if you only care about the brain.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* =========================================================== SHELF
       Visible only on lg+ (≥1024px). The 3D shelf is desktop-only by
       design — opening a 800px book on a 768px tablet would overflow.
       The fallback below renders the same content as plain cards. */}
  <section class="library-shelf mx-auto hidden max-w-6xl px-4 lg:block sm:px-6">
    <div class="shelf-stage">
      <div class="shelf">
        <div class="shelf-glow"></div>
        <div class="shelf-plank"></div>

        {/* Volume 1 */}
        <div class="shelf-book b1" data-vol="b1">
          <div class="spine">
            <div class="spine-content">
              <div class="spine-num">I</div>
              <div class="spine-title">From Zero to Grid</div>
              <div class="spine-mark">B·H·AI</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="book-open-content">
            <div class="open-cover" style="background-image: url('/cover_vol1_final.jpg');"></div>
            <div class="open-details">
              <div class="open-numeral">I</div>
              <div class="open-meta">
                <span class="accent">Volume I</span>
                <span>2026</span>
                <span>23 sessions</span>
                <span>95 pages</span>
                <span>PDF</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="open-title">From Zero to Grid</h2>
              <p class="open-subtitle">When "buy low, sell high" became code.</p>
              <p class="open-pull">"From 'what's an API' to live automated trading. Every mistake, every breakthrough."</p>
              <p class="open-desc">Volume I documents the transition from idea to running system — choosing the stack, designing the grid architecture, debugging at 2AM, learning why the gap between trading theory and trading code is wider than it looks.</p>
              <div class="open-ctas">
                <a class="book-btn book-btn-primary"
                   href="https://payhip.com/b/a4yMc"
                   target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                   data-umami-event="buy-click"
                   data-umami-event-source="library-shelf-v1">
                  €4.99 · Payhip ↗
                </a>
                <a class="book-btn book-btn-secondary"
                   href="https://payhip.com/preview/a4yMc"
                   target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                   data-umami-event="preview-click"
                   data-umami-event-source="library-shelf-v1">
                  ↓ Free preview
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Volume 2 (default open) */}
        <div class="shelf-book b2 open" data-vol="b2">
          <div class="spine">
            <div class="spine-content">
              <div class="spine-num">II</div>
              <div class="spine-title">From Grid to Brain</div>
              <div class="spine-mark">B·H·AI</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="book-open-content">
            <div class="open-cover" style="background-image: url('/cover_vol2_final.jpg');"></div>
            <div class="open-details">
              <div class="open-numeral">II</div>
              <div class="open-meta">
                <span class="accent">Volume II</span>
                <span>2026</span>
                <span>29 sessions</span>
                <span>108 pages</span>
                <span>PDF</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="open-title">From Grid to Brain</h2>
              <p class="open-subtitle">When the bot stopped following rules and started picking coins.</p>
              <p class="open-pull">"29 sessions of getting it wrong, then less wrong, then occasionally right."</p>
              <p class="open-desc">Volume II is the chapter where the system grew a brain — an AI-driven scanner that ranks coins by signal strength, allocates capital across volume tiers, and rotates positions when the trend shifts. Every loss documented, every lesson kept.</p>
              <div class="open-ctas">
                <a class="book-btn book-btn-primary"
                   href="https://payhip.com/b/NHw53"
                   target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                   data-umami-event="buy-click"
                   data-umami-event-source="library-shelf-v2">
                  €4.99 · Payhip ↗
                </a>
                <a class="book-btn book-btn-secondary"
                   href="https://payhip.com/preview/NHw53"
                   target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                   data-umami-event="preview-click"
                   data-umami-event-source="library-shelf-v2">
                  ↓ Free preview
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Volume 3 */}
        <div class="shelf-book b3" data-vol="b3">
          <div class="spine">
            <div class="spine-content">
              <div class="spine-num">III</div>
              <div class="spine-title">From Brain to Reality</div>
              <div class="spine-mark">SOON</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="book-open-content">
            <div class="open-cover placeholder">
              <div class="ph-num">III</div>
              <div class="ph-text">Cover · Coming</div>
            </div>
            <div class="open-details">
              <div class="open-numeral">III</div>
              <div class="open-meta">
                <span>Volume III</span>
                <span>In progress</span>
                <span>ETA TBD</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="open-title">From Brain to Reality</h2>
              <p class="open-subtitle">The bot trades. The brain thinks. Now the question.</p>
              <p class="open-pull">"Does any of it actually make money?"</p>
              <p class="open-desc">Volume III will document the next chapter — taking the autonomous brain to live capital, measuring what's real, killing what isn't.</p>
              <div class="v3-state">⌛ Cover &amp; release date pending</div>
              <div class="open-ctas">
                <a class="book-btn book-btn-secondary"
                   href="https://t.me/BagHolderAI_report"
                   target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                  📡 Notify me on Telegram
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ========================================== SHELF FALLBACK (<lg) */}
  {/* Plain card stack for tablet & mobile. Standard fund palette,
      no Fraunces, no 3D. Same content as the shelf above. */}
  <section class="mx-auto mt-8 max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:hidden">
    <div class="space-y-5">

      {/* Volume 1 */}
      <article class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface
                      sm:grid sm:grid-cols-[200px_1fr]">
        <div class="aspect-[3/4] w-full bg-cover bg-center sm:aspect-auto sm:h-full"
             style="background-image: url('/cover_vol1_final.jpg');"></div>
        <div class="p-5 sm:p-6">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-3 gap-y-1 font-mono text-[10px]
                      uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-text-muted">
            <span class="text-pos">Volume I</span>
            <span class="text-border">·</span>
            <span>2026</span>
            <span class="text-border">·</span>
            <span>23 sessions</span>
            <span class="text-border">·</span>
            <span>95 pages</span>
            <span class="text-border">·</span>
            <span>PDF</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-[22px] font-semibold leading-tight text-text">
            From Zero to Grid
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-[14px] italic text-text-dim">
            When "buy low, sell high" became code.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 border-l-2 border-pos pl-3 text-[14px] leading-[1.55] text-text">
            "From 'what's an API' to live automated trading. Every
            mistake, every breakthrough."
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[14px] leading-[1.6] text-text-dim">
            Volume I documents the transition from idea to running
            system — choosing the stack, designing the grid
            architecture, debugging at 2AM.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
            <a href="https://payhip.com/b/a4yMc"
               target="_blank" rel="noopener"
               data-umami-event="buy-click"
               data-umami-event-source="library-card-v1"
               class="rounded-md bg-pos px-4 py-2 font-mono text-[11px] font-semibold
                      uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-bg
                      transition-colors hover:bg-pos/90">
              €4.99 · Payhip ↗
            </a>
            <a href="https://payhip.com/preview/a4yMc"
               target="_blank" rel="noopener"
               data-umami-event="preview-click"
               data-umami-event-source="library-card-v1"
               class="rounded-md border border-border-soft px-4 py-2
                      font-mono text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em]
                      text-text-dim transition-colors
                      hover:border-text-muted hover:text-text">
              ↓ Free preview
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      {/* Volume 2 */}
      <article class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-neu/30
                      bg-surface ring-1 ring-neu/10
                      sm:grid sm:grid-cols-[200px_1fr]">
        <div class="aspect-[3/4] w-full bg-cover bg-center sm:aspect-auto sm:h-full"
             style="background-image: url('/cover_vol2_final.jpg');"></div>
        <div class="p-5 sm:p-6">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-3 gap-y-1 font-mono text-[10px]
                      uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-text-muted">
            <span class="text-neu">Volume II · live</span>
            <span class="text-border">·</span>
            <span>2026</span>
            <span class="text-border">·</span>
            <span>29 sessions</span>
            <span class="text-border">·</span>
            <span>108 pages</span>
            <span class="text-border">·</span>
            <span>PDF</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-[22px] font-semibold leading-tight text-text">
            From Grid to Brain
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-[14px] italic text-text-dim">
            When the bot stopped following rules and started picking
            coins.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 border-l-2 border-neu pl-3 text-[14px] leading-[1.55] text-text">
            "29 sessions of getting it wrong, then less wrong, then
            occasionally right."
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[14px] leading-[1.6] text-text-dim">
            Volume II is the chapter where the system grew a brain — an
            AI-driven scanner that ranks coins by signal strength,
            allocates capital across volume tiers, and rotates
            positions when the trend shifts. Every loss documented,
            every lesson kept.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
            <a href="https://payhip.com/b/NHw53"
               target="_blank" rel="noopener"
               data-umami-event="buy-click"
               data-umami-event-source="library-card-v2"
               class="rounded-md bg-neu px-4 py-2 font-mono text-[11px] font-semibold
                      uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-bg
                      transition-colors hover:bg-neu/90">
              €4.99 · Payhip ↗
            </a>
            <a href="https://payhip.com/preview/NHw53"
               target="_blank" rel="noopener"
               data-umami-event="preview-click"
               data-umami-event-source="library-card-v2"
               class="rounded-md border border-border-soft px-4 py-2
                      font-mono text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em]
                      text-text-dim transition-colors
                      hover:border-text-muted hover:text-text">
              ↓ Free preview
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      {/* Volume 3 */}
      <article class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-border-soft bg-surface/60
                      sm:grid sm:grid-cols-[200px_1fr]">
        <div class="flex aspect-[3/4] w-full flex-col items-center justify-center
                    gap-3 border-b border-dashed border-border-soft bg-bg/40 p-5
                    sm:aspect-auto sm:h-full sm:border-b-0 sm:border-r">
          <div class="font-serif text-[64px] italic leading-none text-text-muted/60">III</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-text-muted">
            cover · coming
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 sm:p-6">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-3 gap-y-1 font-mono text-[10px]
                      uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-text-muted">
            <span>Volume III</span>
            <span class="text-border">·</span>
            <span>in progress</span>
            <span class="text-border">·</span>
            <span>ETA TBD</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-[22px] font-semibold leading-tight text-text">
            From Brain to Reality
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-[14px] italic text-text-dim">
            The bot trades. The brain thinks. Now the question.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 border-l-2 border-border pl-3 text-[14px] leading-[1.55] text-text">
            "Does any of it actually make money?"
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[14px] leading-[1.6] text-text-dim">
            Volume III will document the next chapter — taking the
            autonomous brain to live capital, measuring what's real,
            killing what isn't.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-4 inline-block rounded border border-border-soft px-3 py-1.5
                      font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-text-muted">
            ⌛ Cover &amp; release date pending
          </div>
          <div class="mt-5">
            <a href="https://t.me/BagHolderAI_report"
               target="_blank" rel="noopener"
               class="rounded-md border border-border-soft px-4 py-2
                      font-mono text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em]
                      text-text-dim transition-colors
                      hover:border-text-muted hover:text-text">
              📡 Notify me on Telegram
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============================================================ MAIN */}
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 pb-24 sm:px-6">

    {/* ============ § 2 — BY THE NUMBERS ============ */}
    <hr class="mt-12 border-t border-border-soft" />
    <section class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="font-mono text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-pos mb-5">
        § 2 · By the numbers
      </h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-px overflow-hidden rounded-lg
                  border border-border bg-border sm:grid-cols-4">
        <div class="bg-surface px-4 py-5 text-center">
          <div class="font-mono text-[24px] font-semibold text-pos tabular-nums">203</div>
          <div class="mt-1 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-text-muted">
            pages
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-surface px-4 py-5 text-center">
          <div class="font-mono text-[24px] font-semibold text-pos tabular-nums">52</div>
          <div class="mt-1 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-text-muted">
            sessions
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-surface px-4 py-5 text-center">
          <div class="font-mono text-[24px] font-semibold text-pos tabular-nums">2</div>
          <div class="mt-1 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-text-muted">
            volumes out
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-surface px-4 py-5 text-center">
          <div class="font-mono text-[24px] font-semibold text-pos tabular-nums">1</div>
          <div class="mt-1 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-text-muted">
            ai ceo
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</Layout>

{/* ====================================================== SCRIPT IMPORT */}
<script>
  import "../scripts/library.ts";
</script>

{/* ====================================================== SCOPED STYLES */}
<style is:inline>
  /* ============================================================
     LIBRARY SHELF — 3D openable books
     Documented exception to STYLEGUIDE §5 (palette tokens) and §6
     (font tokens). The shelf is a "library showcase" with its own
     visual language — Fraunces serif + jewel-tone book covers.
     All selectors are scoped under .library-shelf to avoid leakage.
     ============================================================ */
  .library-shelf {
    --display: 'Fraunces', 'Times New Roman', serif;
    --book-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', 'SF Mono', 'Menlo', monospace;
    --book-cyan: #67e8f9;        /* matches site --neu */
    --book-cyan-dim: rgba(103, 232, 249, 0.45);
    --book-green: #86efac;       /* matches site --pos */
    --shelf-wood: linear-gradient(180deg, #1a1410 0%, #100c0a 60%, #060403 100%);
  }

  .library-shelf .shelf-stage {
    position: relative;
    perspective: 2000px;
    perspective-origin: 50% 70%;
    padding: 16px 0 0;
    margin-bottom: 60px;
  }
  .library-shelf .shelf {
    position: relative;
    height: 540px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: flex-end;
    gap: 0;
    transform-style: preserve-3d;
  }
  .library-shelf .shelf-plank {
    position: absolute;
    left: -8%; right: -8%; bottom: -32px;
    height: 40px;
    background: var(--shelf-wood);
    transform: rotateX(58deg);
    transform-origin: top center;
    box-shadow: 0 30px 60px -10px rgba(0,0,0,0.85), inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border-radius: 1px;
  }
  .library-shelf .shelf-plank::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute; inset: 0;
    background:
      repeating-linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 0px, rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 80px),
      repeating-linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(0,0,0,0.4) 0px, rgba(0,0,0,0.4) 2px, transparent 2px, transparent 240px);
    mix-blend-mode: overlay;
  }
  .library-shelf .shelf-plank::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute; left: 0; right: 0; top: 0; height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(255,255,255,0.08) 30%, rgba(255,255,255,0.08) 70%, transparent);
  }
  .library-shelf .shelf-glow {
    position: absolute;
    left: 20%; right: 20%; top: -40px;
    height: 80px;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, rgba(234,179,8,0.06), transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: -1;
  }

  .library-shelf .shelf-book {
    position: relative;
    width: 80px;
    height: 500px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transform-style: preserve-3d;
    transition:
      width 0.75s cubic-bezier(0.65, 0.05, 0.36, 1),
      transform 0.75s cubic-bezier(0.65, 0.05, 0.36, 1),
      margin 0.75s cubic-bezier(0.65, 0.05, 0.36, 1);
  }
  .library-shelf .shelf-book + .shelf-book { margin-left: 5px; }
  .library-shelf .shelf-book.open {
    width: 800px;
    cursor: default;
    transform: translateZ(50px);
    margin-left: 22px;
    margin-right: 22px;
  }
  .library-shelf .shelf-book.open + .shelf-book { margin-left: 22px; }

  .library-shelf .shelf-book .spine {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    border-radius: 1px 3px 3px 1px;
    transform-style: preserve-3d;
    box-shadow:
      inset -3px 0 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.6),
      inset 3px 0 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.05),
      0 8px 30px -6px rgba(0,0,0,0.8),
      0 30px 50px -20px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
    transition: opacity 0.4s ease;
  }
  .library-shelf .shelf-book.b1 .spine {
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(134,239,172,0.18), rgba(0,0,0,0)),
      linear-gradient(90deg, #0e1d12 0%, #182a1d 50%, #0a160e 100%);
  }
  .library-shelf .shelf-book.b2 .spine {
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(103,232,249,0.22), rgba(0,0,0,0)),
      linear-gradient(90deg, #0a1c20 0%, #0f2c33 50%, #061418 100%);
  }
  .library-shelf .shelf-book.b3 .spine {
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.06), rgba(0,0,0,0)),
      linear-gradient(90deg, #161616 0%, #1f1f1f 50%, #0d0d0d 100%);
  }
  .library-shelf .shelf-book .spine::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute; left: 8px; right: 8px;
    top: 22px; height: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(255,255,255,0.22), transparent);
  }
  .library-shelf .shelf-book .spine::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute; left: 8px; right: 8px;
    bottom: 28px; height: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(255,255,255,0.2), transparent);
  }
  .library-shelf .spine-content {
    position: absolute; inset: 0;
